   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Train, Validation, and Test Split\n",
    "\n",
    "We extract the user-item-rating interactions and split the data into training, validation, and test sets (70/15/15). The original row index is preserved during splitting to help detect potential data leakage before being dropped after the split is completed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "train-test-split",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ratings = df[['userid', 'movieid', 'rating']].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# IMPORTANT: preserve original index for leakage check\n",
    "ratings = ratings.reset_index()  # keeps original row id in 'index' column\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split\n",
    "train_data, temp_data = train_test_split(ratings, test_size=0.30, random_state=42)\n",
    "val_data, test_data = train_test_split(temp_data, test_size=0.50, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Now safe to drop index for modeling\n",
    "train_data = train_data.drop(columns=['index']).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "val_data   = val_data.drop(columns=['index']).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "test_data  = test_data.drop(columns=['index']).reset_index(drop=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "428aab78",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Training Set Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "We compute global and bias statistics using only the training data to avoid data leakage. These values are used across all models to capture user and item tendencies. They also support cold-start handling when users or movies are not present in the training set."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "bias-stats",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Global mean rating (train): 3.4727\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Training-set statistics (used by all models) \n",
    "#  Computed from train_data ONLY — never from val or test.\n",
    "\n",
    "global_mean  = train_data['rating'].mean()\n",
    "user_biases  = train_data.groupby('userid')['rating'].mean()  - global_mean\n",
    "item_biases  = train_data.groupby('movieid')['rating'].mean() - global_mean\n",
    "movie_mean   = train_data.groupby('movieid')['rating'].mean()   # for cold-start\n",
    "user_mean    = train_data.groupby('userid')['rating'].mean()    # for cold-start\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Global mean rating (train): {global_mean:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "sec2-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## Model 1: SVD Collaborative Filtering\n",
    "\n",
    "**Approach:**  \n",
    "1. Normalise ratings by removing global mean + user bias + item bias  \n",
    "2. Apply Truncated SVD to the doubly-normalised user-item matrix  \n",
    "3. At prediction time, reconstruct: `ŷ = global_mean + user_bias + item_bias + latent_pred`  \n",
    "4. Clip to [1, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "**Evaluation uses `test_data` only.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8d251406",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Normalized Training Matrix Construction\n",
    "\n",
    "We build a doubly-normalized rating matrix by removing global, user, and item biases from the training ratings. This helps center the data and improves collaborative filtering performance. The cleaned data is then pivoted into a user–movie matrix, where missing values are filled with zeros."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "svd-train",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Training matrix: (610, 6321)  (users × movies)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Build doubly-normalised training matrix \n",
    "\n",
    "train_data_norm = train_data.copy()\n",
    "train_data_norm['rating'] = train_data_norm.apply(\n",
    "    lambda r: r['rating']\n",
    "              - global_mean\n",
    "              - user_biases.get(r['userid'],  0)\n",
    "              - item_biases.get(r['movieid'], 0),\n",
    "    axis=1\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "train_matrix = train_data_norm.pivot_table(\n",
    "    index='userid', columns='movieid', values='rating'\n",
    ").fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Training matrix: {train_matrix.shape}  (users × movies)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dcd96196",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### SVD Model Training (Collaborative Filtering)\n",
    "\n",
    "We train a Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) model using a truncated matrix factorization approach. The number of latent factors is capped at 600 (or adjusted based on dataset size). The model learns compressed user and item representations, which are then used to reconstruct predicted ratings. We also report the total explained variance to assess how much information is retained by the latent factors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "svd-fit",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "SVD fitted — 600 components\n",
      "Explained variance: 99.99%\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Fit SVD\n",
    "#  n_components = 600 latent factors (as in original)\n",
    "\n",
    "N_COMPONENTS = min(600, min(train_matrix.shape) - 1)  # guard for small datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "svd_model = TruncatedSVD(n_components=N_COMPONENTS, random_state=42)\n",
    "U  = svd_model.fit_transform(train_matrix)\n",
    "Vt = svd_model.components_\n",
    "\n",
    "pred_matrix_norm = U @ Vt\n",
    "pred_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    pred_matrix_norm,\n",
    "    index=train_matrix.index,\n",
    "    columns=train_matrix.columns\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"SVD fitted — {N_COMPONENTS} components\")\n",
    "print(f\"Explained variance: {svd_model.explained_variance_ratio_.sum():.2%}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c5337b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### SVD Prediction Function\n",
    "\n",
    "We define a prediction function that reconstructs user–movie ratings using the learned SVD components. The final prediction combines the global mean, user bias, item bias, and latent interaction terms. For unseen users or items, the model falls back to the global mean. All predictions are clipped to the valid rating range (1–5) for consistency."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "svd-predict-fn",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# SVD prediction function \n",
    "\n",
    "def svd_predict(user_id: int, movie_id: int) -> float:\n",
    "\n",
    "    if user_id not in pred_df.index or movie_id not in pred_df.columns:\n",
    "        return float(global_mean)  # unseen → fallback\n",
    "\n",
    "    latent = pred_df.loc[user_id, movie_id]\n",
    "    pred   = (global_mean\n",
    "              + user_biases.get(user_id,  0)\n",
    "              + item_biases.get(movie_id, 0)\n",
    "              + latent)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return float(np.clip(pred, RATING_MIN, RATING_MAX))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "411d8657",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Ranking Metrics for Model Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "We define shared evaluation utilities used across all recommendation models. The metrics focus on ranking quality rather than raw prediction error. Specifically, we compute Precision@K, Recall@K, Hit Rate, and NDCG@K to measure how well the model ranks relevant items for each user. These functions are applied consistently to ensure fair comparison between models."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "ranking-metrics-fn",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# These functions are reused across all three models.\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_ndcg(relevance: list, k: int) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Normalised Discounted Cumulative Gain at k.\"\"\"\n",
    "    dcg  = sum(r / np.log2(i + 2) for i, r in enumerate(relevance[:k]))\n",
    "    idcg = sum(r / np.log2(i + 2) for i, r in enumerate(sorted(relevance, reverse=True)[:k]))\n",
    "    return dcg / idcg if idcg > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def ranking_metrics(predict_fn, data: pd.DataFrame, k: int = 5,\n",
    "                    threshold: float = 4.0) -> dict:\n",
    "    \n",
    "    precisions, recalls, hits, ndcgs = [], [], [], []\n",
    "\n",
    "    for user_id, group in data.groupby('userid'):\n",
    "        if len(group) < 2:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        relevant_movies = set(group.loc[group['rating'] >= threshold, 'movieid'])\n",
    "        if len(relevant_movies) == 0:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Score all movies this user interacted with in the evaluation set\n",
    "        candidates = group['movieid'].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "        scored = sorted(\n",
    "            [(m, predict_fn(user_id, m)) for m in candidates],\n",
    "            key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        top_k = [m for m, _ in scored[:k]]\n",
    "        relevance = [1 if m in relevant_movies else 0 for m in top_k]\n",
    "\n",
    "        n_relevant_total = len(relevant_movies)\n",
    "\n",
    "        precisions.append(sum(relevance) / k)\n",
    "        recalls.append(sum(relevance) / n_relevant_total)\n",
    "        hits.append(int(any(relevance)))\n",
    "        ndcgs.append(compute_ndcg(relevance, k))\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        f'Precision@{k}': np.mean(precisions),\n",
    "        f'Recall@{k}':    np.mean(recalls),\n",
    "        f'HitRate@{k}':   np.mean(hits),\n",
    "        f'NDCG@{k}':      np.mean(ndcgs),\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "svd-eval",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "SVD Collaborative Filtering — Test Metrics\n",
      "  RMSE           : 0.3495\n",
      "  MAE            : 0.1000\n",
      "  Precision@5    : 0.9163\n",
      "  Recall@5       : 0.6076\n",
      "  HitRate@5      : 1.0000\n",
