   "source": [
    "\n",
    "#### Movie Title–ID Mapping and Lookup Function\n",
    "\n",
    "We create mapping dictionaries to enable fast conversion between movie titles and movie IDs. First, we build a clean mapping from `movieid` to `clean_title`, then invert it to create a title-to-ID dictionary with standardized formatting (lowercased and stripped). A helper function is also defined to safely retrieve a movie ID from a given title using this mapping."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "cb81905b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_movie_id(title: str):\n",
    "    title = title.lower().strip()\n",
    "    return title_to_movieid.get(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create global title mappings (SAFE FIX)\n",
    "movie_titles = df[['movieid', 'clean_title']].drop_duplicates()\n",
    "\n",
    "movieid_to_title = dict(zip(movie_titles['movieid'], movie_titles['clean_title']))\n",
    "title_to_movieid = {v.lower().strip(): k for k, v in movieid_to_title.items()}    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b5d2dcbd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### SVD-Based Movie Recommendation by Title\n",
    "\n",
    "We define a recommendation function that generates movie suggestions based on a given movie title using the SVD collaborative filtering model. The process works as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "First, the movie title is converted into its corresponding movie ID. Then, we identify users in the training data who liked that movie (ratings ≥ 4). For each of these users, we predict ratings for all other movies using the trained SVD model. The scores are averaged across users to produce a final ranking. The top-K highest scoring movies are selected and converted back into readable movie titles for interpretation.\n",
    "\n",
    "This approach captures **user similarity patterns through shared preferences**, making recommendations more personalized and context-aware."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "5cd6a863",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def recommend_movies_svd_by_title(title: str, top_k: int = 5):\n",
    "    movie_id = get_movie_id(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if movie_id is None:\n",
    "        print(\"Movie not found in dataset.\")\n",
    "        return []\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Step 1: find users who liked this movie (from TRAIN data only)\n",
    "    users_who_liked = train_data[\n",
    "        (train_data['movieid'] == movie_id) &\n",
    "        (train_data['rating'] >= 4)\n",
    "    ]['userid'].unique()\n",
    "\n",
    "    if len(users_who_liked) == 0:\n",
    "        print(\"No users found who liked this movie.\")\n",
    "        return []\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Step 2: score ALL movies for these users\n",
    "    movie_scores = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "    for user in users_who_liked:\n",
    "        for m in pred_df.columns:\n",
    "            if m == movie_id:\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "\n",
    "            score = svd_predict(user, m)\n",
    "\n",
    "            if m not in movie_scores:\n",
    "                movie_scores[m] = []\n",
    "            movie_scores[m].append(score)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Step 3: average scores across users\n",
    "    avg_scores = {\n",
    "        m: np.mean(scores)\n",
    "        for m, scores in movie_scores.items()\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Step 4: sort and pick top_k\n",
    "    top_movies = sorted(avg_scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:top_k]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Step 5: convert to titles\n",
    "    recommendations = [\n",
    "        (movieid_to_title.get(m, \"Unknown\"), score)\n",
    "        for m, score in top_movies\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    return recommendations"
   ]
  },
