   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "sec3-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Model 2: Content-Based Filtering\n",
    "\n",
    "We build a content-based recommendation system using movie metadata. First, we remove duplicate movies and construct a clean dataset. We then transform the combined text features using TF-IDF to capture important word-level patterns while filtering out common and uninformative terms.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next, we reduce the high-dimensional TF-IDF representation using SVD to obtain a compact latent feature space. Cosine similarity is then computed between all movie vectors to measure content similarity.\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, we create helper mappings between movie IDs, titles, and matrix indices to support efficient lookup during recommendation. This pipeline enables similarity-based recommendations using movie content features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "content-build",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Content matrix: (6834, 100)  (movies × latent dims)\n",
      "Similarity matrix: (6834, 6834)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "movie_content = df.drop_duplicates(subset='movieid').reset_index(drop=True).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# TF-IDF\n",
    "tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(\n",
    "    max_features=5000,\n",
    "    stop_words='english',\n",
    "    min_df=2,\n",
    "    max_df=0.85,\n",
    "    ngram_range=(1, 2)\n",
    ")\n",
    "tfidf_matrix = tfidf.fit_transform(movie_content['content'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dimensionality reduction\n",
    "content_svd = TruncatedSVD(n_components=100, random_state=42)\n",
    "reduced_matrix = content_svd.fit_transform(tfidf_matrix)  # shape: (n_movies, 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cosine similarity\n",
    "content_similarity = cosine_similarity(reduced_matrix)     # shape: (n_movies, n_movies)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Index helpers\n",
    "movieid_to_idx  = {mid: i for i, mid in enumerate(movie_content['movieid'])}\n",
    "idx_to_movieid  = {i: mid for mid, i in movieid_to_idx.items()}\n",
    "movieid_to_title = movie_content.set_index('movieid')['clean_title'].to_dict()\n",
    "title_to_movieid = {v: k for k, v in movieid_to_title.items()}\n",
    "title_to_idx     = {t: movieid_to_idx[mid] for t, mid in title_to_movieid.items()\n",
    "                    if mid in movieid_to_idx}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Content matrix: {reduced_matrix.shape}  (movies × latent dims)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Similarity matrix: {content_similarity.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1f6b0e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Content-Based Model Prediction and Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "We define a content-based prediction function that estimates a user’s rating for a movie based on the similarity between movie content features. The model compares the target movie with movies the user has previously rated using cosine similarity and computes a weighted average of the user’s past ratings.\n",
    "\n",
    "To evaluate the model, we generate predictions for the test set and compute standard error metrics (RMSE and MAE) as well as ranking metrics such as Precision@K, Recall@K, Hit Rate, and NDCG. These results help assess both rating accuracy and recommendation quality."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "content-predict-fn",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def content_predict(user_id: int, movie_id: int) -> float:\n",
    "    if movie_id not in movieid_to_idx:\n",
    "        return float(global_mean)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if user_id not in user_history_map:\n",
    "        return float(global_mean)\n",
    "\n",
    "    target_idx = movieid_to_idx[movie_id]\n",
    "    history = user_history_map[user_id]\n",
    "\n",
    "    sims = []\n",
    "    ratings = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    for hist_movie, rating in history:\n",
    "        if hist_movie == movie_id:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        if hist_movie not in movieid_to_idx:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        hist_idx = movieid_to_idx[hist_movie]\n",
    "        sims.append(content_similarity[target_idx, hist_idx])\n",
    "        ratings.append(rating)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if len(sims) == 0:\n",
    "        return float(global_mean)\n",
    "\n",
    "    sims = np.array(sims)\n",
    "    ratings = np.array(ratings)\n",
    "\n",
    "    pred = np.dot(sims, ratings) / (np.sum(sims) + 1e-8)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return float(np.clip(pred, RATING_MIN, RATING_MAX))"
   ]
  },
