  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9360b17c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Content-Based Movie Recommendation \n",
    "\n",
    "We define a content-based recommendation function that generates similar movies based on a given movie title. The process begins by converting the title into its corresponding index in the similarity matrix. We then retrieve cosine similarity scores between the selected movie and all other movies. The most similar movies are identified by sorting these scores in descending order while excluding the input movie itself. Finally, the top-K most similar movies are mapped back to their titles and returned as recommendations with their similarity scores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "9f61d8a2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_movie_idx_from_title(title: str):\n",
    "    title = title.lower().strip()\n",
    "    if title not in title_to_idx:\n",
    "        print(\"Movie not found.\")\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    return title_to_idx[title]\n",
    "\n",
    "def recommend_movies_content(title: str, top_k: int = 5):\n",
    "    idx = get_movie_idx_from_title(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if idx is None:\n",
    "        return []\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Get similarity scores for this movie\n",
    "    sim_scores = content_similarity[idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Get top similar movie indices (excluding itself)\n",
    "    similar_indices = np.argsort(sim_scores)[::-1][1:top_k+1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Convert to titles\n",
    "    recommendations = [\n",
    "        (movieid_to_title[idx_to_movieid[i]], sim_scores[i])\n",
    "        for i in similar_indices\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    return recommendations"
   ]
  },
