   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Model 3: Hybrid Recommendation Model (SVD + Content-Based)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "464c12f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "We implement a hybrid recommendation model that combines predictions from the SVD collaborative filtering model and the content-based model. The final score is computed as a weighted average controlled by the parameter α (alpha), where SVD contributes more heavily when α is closer to 1.\n",
    "\n",
    "The hybrid model is evaluated on the test set using both prediction error metrics (RMSE and MAE) and ranking metrics (Precision@K, Recall@K, Hit Rate, and NDCG). This allows us to assess both rating accuracy and recommendation quality.\n",
    "\n",
    "Overall, the hybrid approach aims to balance:\n",
    "- **SVD strength:** capturing user–item interaction patterns\n",
    "- **Content-based strength:** handling item similarity and cold-start cases"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "hybrid-eval-default",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "── Hybrid (α=0.7) — Test Metrics ──\n",
      "RMSE           : 0.4203\n",
      "MAE            : 0.2792\n",
      "Precision@5    : 0.9183\n",
      "Recall@5       : 0.6085\n",
      "HitRate@5      : 1.0000\n",
      "NDCG@5         : 0.9900\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def hybrid_predict(user_id: int, movie_id: int, alpha: float = 0.7) -> float:\n",
    "    svd_score = svd_predict(user_id, movie_id)\n",
    "    content_score = content_predict(user_id, movie_id)\n",
    "\n",
    "    blended = alpha * svd_score + (1 - alpha) * content_score\n",
    "    return float(np.clip(blended, RATING_MIN, RATING_MAX))\n",
    "\n",
    "DEFAULT_ALPHA = 0.7\n",
    "\n",
    "hybrid_preds = np.array([\n",
    "    hybrid_predict(u, m, DEFAULT_ALPHA)\n",
    "    for u, m in zip(test_data.userid, test_data.movieid)\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "hybrid_actuals = test_data['rating'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "hyb_rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(hybrid_actuals, hybrid_preds))\n",
    "hyb_mae  = mean_absolute_error(hybrid_actuals, hybrid_preds)\n",
    "\n",
    "hyb_ranking = ranking_metrics(\n",
    "    lambda u, m: hybrid_predict(u, m, DEFAULT_ALPHA),\n",
    "    test_data,\n",
    "    k=K\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "hybrid_metrics_default = {'RMSE': hyb_rmse, 'MAE': hyb_mae, **hyb_ranking}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"── Hybrid (α={DEFAULT_ALPHA}) — Test Metrics ──\")\n",
    "for m, v in hybrid_metrics_default.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"{m:<15}: {v:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
