    "\n",
    "## Cold-Start Handling "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cd32083e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "We define a unified prediction function to handle cold-start scenarios where users or movies are not present in the training data. When both user and movie are known, the model uses the standard hybrid prediction.\n",
    "\n",
    "For unseen cases:\n",
    "- **New user:** fallback to the movie’s average rating  \n",
    "- **New movie:** fallback to the user’s average rating  \n",
    "- **Both unseen:** fallback to the global mean  \n",
    "\n",
    "This approach ensures stable and reasonable predictions even when insufficient historical data is available."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "0c3f3f15",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#  Sets of users and items known at training time\n",
    "\n",
    "train_users  = set(train_data['userid'])\n",
    "train_movies = set(train_data['movieid'])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cold-start prediction function \n",
    "\n",
    "def cold_start_predict(user_id: int, movie_id: int, alpha: float = None) -> float:\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if alpha is None:\n",
    "        alpha = best_alpha\n",
    "\n",
    "    user_known  = user_id  in train_users\n",
    "    movie_known = movie_id in train_movies\n",
    "\n",
    "    if user_known and movie_known:\n",
    "        # Standard path — both known\n",
    "        return hybrid_predict(user_id, movie_id, alpha)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not user_known and movie_known:\n",
    "        # New user — fall back to item mean or global mean\n",
    "        return float(movie_mean.get(movie_id, global_mean))\n",
    "\n",
    "    if user_known and not movie_known:\n",
    "        # New movie — fall back to user mean or global mean\n",
    "        return float(user_mean.get(user_id, global_mean))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Both unknown\n",
    "    return float(global_mean)"
   ]
  },
